1. The least squares (LS) mean ADHD-RS-IV total score changes from baseline to end of treatment with placebo was -17.0 ± 1.03 in the forced-dose study.
2. The LS mean ADHD-RS-IV total score changes from baseline to end of treatment with LDX was -25.4 ± 0.74 in the forced-dose study.
3. The LS mean ADHD-RS-IV total score changes from baseline to end of treatment with OROS-MPH was -22.1 ± 0.73 in the forced-dose study.
4. The LS mean ADHD-RS-IV total score changes from baseline to end of treatment with placebo was -13.4 ± 1.19 in the flexible-dose study.
5. The LS mean ADHD-RS-IV total score changes from baseline to end of treatment with LDX was -25.6 ± 0.82 in the flexible-dose study.
6. The LS mean ADHD-RS-IV total score changes from baseline to end of treatment with OROS-MPH was -23.5 ± 0.80 in the flexible-dose study.
7. The study was conducted in two different dosing methods: forced-dose and flexible-dose.
8. Three different treatments were used in the study: placebo, LDX, and OROS-MPH.
9. The study measured the ADHD-RS-IV total score changes from baseline to end of treatment.

messages.content:
